hasMenuItem.name: 3 Course Dinner
hasMenuItem.description:
Starters: 
- Caesar salad: Romaine lettuce, golden croutons, house dressing.
- Kalamari: Marinated, golden crispy.
- Mini Spanakopita: Spinach, feta, herbs, phyllo pastry.

Mains:
- Kleftiko: Slow roasted lamb shoulder, Greek herbs.
- Chicken & prawn souvlaki: Two skewers, marinated prawns & chicken.
- Filet of salmon: Wild salmon, white wine dill shrimp sauce.
- Spanakota: Chicken breast, spinach & feta, white wine cream sauce.
- Lamb Exohiko: Roast lamb, peppers, onions, cheeses, phyllo pastry.

Desserts:
- Ravani: Orange sponge cake, orange syrup, whipped cream.
- Mini Bougatsa: Hot custard cream, phyllo pastry, icing sugar & cinnamon.
- Ekmek: Custard layers, syrup-soaked rusks, whipped cream, nuts.

review.reviewBody: This has always been our favorite restaurant and it did not disappoint! Huge portions, and all of it was absolutely delicious. The Kleftiko and the lamb souvlaki were the best part.
The large souvlaki was very good. Great size portion with 2 skewers of chicken.
We've ordered Souvlaki from other local greek restaurants recently and the chicken, rice, and potatoes are our favorites from here .  The Tsatziki isn't our fave, but the rest of the fare is great.

One of the best places in White Rock for Greek food!
Always excellent :)
the salad was a bit watery and lacked flavor of dressing
